    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan I've created:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public API\n\n### What I Found\n\n- **`src/ini.zig`** already contains a fully-featured INI parser (`bun.ini.Parser`) — no need to write one from scratch\n- **`bun.zig` line 230** exposes it as `pub const ini = @import(\"./ini.zig\")`, making it accessible as `bun.ini.Parser`\n- **`IniTestingAPIs.parse`** (`src/ini.zig:674`) shows the exact pattern for calling the parser from a JS function, including the `globalThis.bunVM().transpiler.env` required by the parser\n- The 6-step wiring pattern (Zig file → api.zig → BunObject.zig → exports.h → BunObject.cpp → bun.d.ts) is consistent across all existing format objects\n\n### 6 Files to Touch\n\n1. **NEW** `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` — `create`, `parse` (reuses `bun.ini.Parser`), `stringify` (self-contained JSValue walker)\n2. `src/bun.js/api.zig` — `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\")`\n3. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — lazy property constant, `@export`, `getINIObject()` getter, import\n4. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5`\n5. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — `INI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback` before `JSONC`\n6. `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` — `namespace INI` with JSDoc for `parse` and `stringify`",
